author: CNN
description: Brian Walshe was convicted of first-degree murder. His Google searches were key evidence, but do they show premeditation? Laura Coates and Jean Casarez break them down. Stream their full conversation now on the CNN app.
title: Lawyers break down Brian Walshe’s search history

author: CNN
description: The Justice Department released a new batch of documents from Epstein investigation. President Donald Trump’s name is mentioned many times in the documents, including in references to flight records related to Epstein’s private plane. Authorities have not accused Trump of criminal wrongdoing related to Epstein. CNN's Marshall Cohen reports.
title: Trump appears in new batch of Epstein documents

author: CNN
description: CNN examines rapper Nicki Minaj’s shift from criticizing Trump’s anti-immigration policies to becoming a full-throated MAGA supporter who openly praises the president.
title: How Nicki Minaj went from Trump critic to fan

author: CNN
description: Popular Kentucky bourbon maker Jim Beam plans to pause production at its main distillery on January 1, according to the James B. Beam Distilling Co.
title: Jim Beam pauses bourbon production at Kentucky distillery

author: CNN
description:
CBS News editor in chief Bari Weiss decided to shelve a planned “60 Minutes” story titled “Inside CECOT,” creating an uproar inside CBS, but the report has reached a worldwide audience anyway. 

On Monday, some Canadian viewers noticed that the pre-planned “60 Minutes” episode was published on a streaming platform owned by Global TV, the network that has the rights to “60 Minutes” in Canada. CNN’s Brian Stelter reports. 

00:00 Live report on controversial ‘60 Minutes’ story accidently being streamed 
00:32 CNN’s chief media analyst with the latest on the viral ‘60 Minutes’ report 
03:38 Former CBS News chief investigative correspondent reacts to the news 

#60Minutes #CBS  #News
title: '60 Minutes’ CECOT episode ‘mistakenly’ streams in Canada

author: CNN
description: New York City’s MetroCard transformed one of the world’s busiest transit systems and is set to be phased out by December 31, 2025. CNN’s Meena Duerson talks about how the MetroCard’s introduction 30 years ago expanded access for New Yorkers, and how the little yellow card has become as symbolic as the city’s famous landmarks. #cnn #news #newyorkcity
title: Goodbye to the MetroCard that transformed how New Yorkers traveled

author: CNN
description: Former Republican Sen. Ben Sasse announced Tuesday that he’s been diagnosed with stage 4 pancreatic cancer. CNN's Brian Todd reports.
title: Ben Sasse announces stage 4 pancreatic cancer diagnosis

author: CNN
description: The Justice Department released more files from the investigation into Jeffrey Epstein that included President Trump's name in multiple documents. Authorities have not accused Trump of criminal wrongdoing related to Epstein and the DOJ said some of the materials include “untrue and sensationalist” claims about the president. CNN's Pamela Brown spoke to Epstein survivor Haley Robson about the files and President Trump's response. #cnn #epsteinfiles #haleyrobson #donaldtrump
title: Epstein survivor calls for Trump's impeachment over handling of investigation

author: CNN
description: North Korea has opened new luxury hotels near the Chinese border. But with foreign tourism still tightly restricted, questions remain over who is actually staying in them. #cnn #news
title: Who’s staying in North Korea’s luxury hotels?

author: CNN
description:
A handwritten letter signed by “J. Epstein” appears to make crude references to President Donald Trump in a short 2019 message from jail addressed to convicted sex offender Larry Nassar. 

The letter does not explicitly name Trump, but instead refers to “our president.” The message appears to have been sent in August 2019, the same month Epstein died by suicide. Trump was president at the time. 

00:00 Live report on DOJ releasing letter from “J. Epstein” to convicted sex offender Larry Nassar 
00:45 Epstein survivor discusses apparent reference to Trump in Larry Nasser letter 
01:25 CNN senior reporter on latest DOJ release of documents related to the Jeffrey Epstein investigation 
05:00 Ex-Watergate prosecutor reacts to apparent reference to Trump in letter to Larry Nassar 

#JeffreyEpstein #LarryNassar   #News
title: Letter signed by ‘J. Epstein’ to Larry Nassar cites ‘our president’

author: CNN
description: Former neighbors paint a mixed portrait of Claudio Neves Valente, whose motives remain a mystery more than a week after police say the suspected shooter killed two Brown University students and an MIT professor, portraying a “very bright” but reclusive young man who was estranged from his family. CNN's Duarte Mendonça reports.
title: CNN visits suspected Brown University shooter's hometown in Portugal

description:
Protests erupted in Albania after weeks of tensions over corruption allegations against the deputy of the country's Prime Minister Belinda Balluku and other officials. This comes after opposition lawmakers scuffled with police inside the Albanian parliament on Thursday, Reuters reports.

#cnn #news #albania
title: Why are there protests in Albania?

author: CNN
description: Each Christmas, letters to Santa pour in from around the world to a small town just outside Oslo. As Richard Quest looks through the mail in Norway, he uncovers an unexpected surprise. #cnn #news

author: CNN
description: A Texas man named Sky Decker jumped into the water to rescue a woman trapped in the wreckage of a Mexican Navy plane that crashed into Galveston Bay. The incident resulted in several fatalities, including a 2-year-old child, according to officials.
title: Bystander rescues woman trapped in plane crash

author: CNN
description: As Ukraine lowers its conscription age to 25, Ukrainian men are fleeing the fighting. CNN's chief international correspondent travels to Romania, where many of the men risk their lives in the rugged hills of the Carpathian mountains to escape the country.
title: Ukrainian men risking death to avoid the frontline

author: CNN
description: In the frigid forests of the Arctic Circle, not far from the border with Russia, CNN's Isobel Yeung sees how Finnish border guards are training for the threat of war. Stream the full story on the CNN app.
title: Preparing for war in the Arctic Circle

author: CNN
description: 78-year-old veteran Charlie Hicks goes to the same restaurant every day and orders the gumbo. When he stopped showing up, the chef went to check on him and ended up saving his life. Chef Donell Stallworth tells CNN's Erin Burnett how a bowl of gumbo helped bring them together.
title: Chef's intuition saved longtime customer who stopped showing up

author: CNN
description: In Newburgh Heights, Ohio, police detained three children for stealing a Kia after a high-speed pursuit. Police say the children learned how to lift the car by watching YouTube tutorials.
title: Three kids steal and crash car after watching YouTube tutorial

description: President Donald Trump unveiled a new “Trump class” of Navy battleships Monday, describing them as a superior war fighting vessel to replace an “old and tired and obsolete” US fleet.
title: Trump reveals new 'Golden Fleet' of battleships

author: CNN
description: President Donald Trump bemoaned the potential reputational damage inflicted on people who appear in photos released as part of the Jeffrey Epstein files, which he insisted were only made public because of an effort to distract from his accomplishments. The comments mark the first time Trump has addressed the files since his Justice Department released hundreds of thousands of them pursuant to a new law compelling them to do so.
title: Trump reacts to photos made public from Epstein files

author: CNN
description: The FDA has approved a daily pill version of Novo Nordisk's weight-loss drug Wegovy, which retains the same active ingredient as the original, allowing for an alternative to the weekly injections currently offered. CNN's Meg Tirrell reports. #cnn #news
title: Approved weight loss pill can be swallowed instead of injected

author: CNN
description: A new mural by elusive British street artist Banksy appeared Monday in London, depicting two children in winter hats lying on the ground.
title: New Banksy artwork pops up in London
